Azerbaijan plans to spend 2.2 billion
manat ($2.8 billion) on industrial and power generation projects
in the next four years, Interfax-Azerbaydzhan reported, citing a
government official it didnâ€™t identify.  The projects include building and modernizing power, waste-
recycling, fertilizer and chemical plants, Interfax said. The
government will spend 266.2 million manat in the next year,
579.2 million manat in 2014, 690 million manat in 2015 and 680
million manat in 2016, the news service said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
